==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gorce
<hw>Gorce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>gort</ets>,
nom. <ets>gorz</ets>, gulf, L. <ets>gurges</ets> whirlpool, gulf,
stream. See <er>Gorge</er>.]</ety> <def>A pool of water to keep fish in;
a wear.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <-- "wear" here is in the sense of
"weir". But why the less-common word? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gorcock</ent>⟦br⟧
